│      // don't account for the poison semantics.                             │
│      if (Pred.hasSameSign())                                                │
│        return nullptr;                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│      Value *X = MinMax->getLHS();                                           │
│      Value *Y = MinMax->getRHS();                                           │
│      if (ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred) && !MinMax->isSigned())                   │
│        return nullptr;                                                      │
│    ```                                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ 5. **Conclusion**: The fix is to bail out early when the predicate has the  │
│ `samesign` flag, since the existing transformation logic doesn't properly   │
│ handle the poison semantics introduced by `samesign`. This prevents the     │
│ incorrect transformation while preserving correct optimizations for         │
│ non-samesign comparisons.                                                   │
